    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL MODEL ES52-7A AND ESO65-7A 6-PLUS - DISASSEMBLY - SHIFT TOWER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SHIFT TOWER</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1300604">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Begin disassembly by cutting the two tie cables which secure the boot.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the boot off the shift lever.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two trunion screws.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the lever from the tower.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the shift yoke from the lever, simply press out the pivot pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wash all parts. Inspect them thoroughly for damage. Replace parts as necessary.</para>
            <figure id="f1300604" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300604" filename="../figg13/G1300604.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Exploded View of Shift Tower</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
